Privacy Policy – Sera Budget

Last updated: 02.12.2025

This Privacy Policy explains how Sera Budget (“the App”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses and protects your information when you use our mobile application.

By using Sera Budget, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Policy.

1. Who We Are

Sera Budget is a mobile application developed by Eren YILDIRIM, based in Türkiye.

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
Email: eerenyiildirim@gmail.com

2. What This Policy Covers

This Privacy Policy applies to:

The Sera Budget Android/iOS application

Any related services, such as cloud sync, premium features and customer support

It does not apply to third-party services that we do not control (for example: your bank, your email provider, or third-party apps).

3. Information We Collect

We design Sera Budget to store budget and subscription data, not sensitive banking credentials. We do not ask for your bank passwords or card PINs.

3.1 Information You Provide

When you use the App, you may provide:

Subscription data
Names of services (e.g. streaming, gym, phone), renewal dates, amounts, currencies, categories and notes.

Expense & budget data
Your manual records of expenses, income, budgets, categories and descriptions.

Reminders & calendar data
Payment due dates, reminder settings and, if you enable calendar sync, event data related to your subscriptions or bills.

Receipts & images (for OCR)
When you use the receipt scanning feature, we process images of receipts or invoices to extract amounts and basic text.

Account / profile data (if applicable)
If the App requires an account or cloud sync, we may collect your email address or username to create and manage your account.

Support messages
If you contact us, we may collect your email address and any information you choose to share in the message.

3.2 Information Collected Automatically

When you use Sera Budget, we may automatically collect:

Device information
Device model, operating system version, language, time zone, app version.

Usage data
In-app interactions such as screens visited, buttons clicked, feature usage, crash logs and performance data.

Approximate location
We may infer approximate region (e.g. country) from your IP address or device settings to apply correct currency or localization. We do not track your precise GPS location.

3.3 Information from Third Parties

We may receive limited information from:

App stores (e.g. Google Play, App Store) – such as purchase status for premium features, refunds and basic install data.

Payment providers – confirmation that a purchase has been completed (we do not receive your full payment card details).

4. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide the core app functionality

Saving your subscriptions, expenses, reminders and settings

Showing totals, reports and analytics inside the App

To provide Premium features

Managing your premium subscription status

Enabling features like advanced reports, themes, biometric app lock, receipt scanning, cloud sync and calendar sync

To sync and back up your data (if cloud sync is enabled)

Storing your data securely on remote servers so you can restore it or use it across devices

To improve the App

Analyzing anonymous usage and crash data to understand which features are used and to fix bugs

To communicate with you

Responding to customer support requests

Sending important notifications about security, updates or changes to this Policy

To show ads (free version only)

If the free version is supported by ads, we may use an ad network that receives technical data to deliver and measure ads.

We do not sell your personal data to third parties.

5. Legal Bases (EU/EEA Users)

If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA) or the UK, we process your personal data on the following legal bases:

Performance of a contract – to provide the App and its features to you

Legitimate interests – to maintain and improve the App, prevent abuse and secure our services

Consent – for optional features such as personalized ads, analytics or specific permissions (e.g. calendar or storage access)

You may withdraw your consent at any time through your device settings or in-app options (where available).

6. How We Share Your Information

We may share your information with:

Service providers

Cloud hosting and database providers

Analytics and crash reporting tools

OCR or image processing services (for receipt scanning)

Payment processors and app stores (for premium subscriptions)

Ad networks (if ads are used)

To deliver, measure and improve ad performance in the free version of the App.

Legal requirements

If required by law or court order, or to respond to lawful requests by public authorities.

We do not share your subscription and expense data with third parties for their own marketing purposes.

7. Data Retention

We retain your information for as long as:

Your account is active (if you use cloud sync/account login), or

It is needed to provide the App and services to you, or

Required by law (for example, for tax or accounting records).

You can request deletion of your data as described in Your Rights below. If you uninstall the App, locally stored data on your device will be removed. Cloud backups may be retained for a limited time in our backups, after which they are deleted or anonymized.

8. Data Security

We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss or misuse, including:

Encrypted communication where applicable

Access controls and authentication

Biometric app lock (if you enable this feature on your device)

However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

9. Your Rights and Choices

Depending on your location, you may have some or all of the following rights regarding your personal data:

Access – request a copy of the personal data we hold about you

Correction – request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data

Deletion – request that we delete your data (subject to legal obligations)

Restriction – request that we limit the processing of your data

Objection – object to certain types of processing (e.g. direct marketing)

Data portability – request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used format

To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [Contact Email]. We may ask you to verify your identity before responding.

You can also control many permissions directly on your device (e.g. camera access for receipts, calendar access, notifications).

10. Children’s Privacy

Sera Budget is not intended for use by children under 13 years of age (or the minimum age required in your country). We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

If you believe that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at [Contact Email], and we will take steps to delete such information.

11. International Data Transfers

Your information may be processed and stored on servers located outside of your country, where data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.

Where required by law, we take appropriate safeguards to protect your information during such transfers.

12. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.

If the changes are material, we may provide additional notice within the App or by other means.

13. Contact Us

If you have any questions, concerns or requests about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you can contact us at:

Eren YILDIRIM
Email: eerenyiildirim@gmail.com
